Dar es Salaam. Local modeling firm Black Fox this week reached a promotional agreement with a new financier David Johnson from the UK who will help promote many up and coming models signed by the company.Speaking at the contract signing owner of Black Fox, Aj Mynah said the agreement will open doors for local aspiring models to showcase themselves beyond the Tanzanian border.Under the agreement models who are assigned by Black Fox will have opportunities of work in Europe and other parts of the world. It is a fact that modeling is not such a big industry in the country, we are of the view that our agreement with David Johnson will help to take Black Fox to international levels and also help millions of youths from within and outside the country, he said .He added that the company s aim is to see that it opens markets for local models in Africa, America and Europe after training many of them in the modeling, marketing and advertising.